BFN 

  [Text] At the request of Peter Boross, President of the 
Republic Arpad Goncz has relieved the administrative state 
secretaries at the Ministries of Defense and Foreign Affairs and 
at the Prime Minister's Office. Rudolf Joo [administrative 
state secretary at the Ministry of Defense], will depart in the 
middle of July, Janos Martonyi [administrative state secretary 
at the Ministry of Foreign Affairs] will leave at the end of 
August, while Jozsef Kajdi [administrative state secretary at 
the Prime Minister's Office] will vacate his office on 10 July. 

